President Trump met with King Abdullah II of Jordan at the National Prayer Breakfast in Washington, D.C. They discussed the U.S.'s commitment to Jordan's stability, security, and prosperity. President Trump thanked the King for his leadership in promoting peace and stability in the region and highlighted Jordan's contributions to defeating ISIS. They also discussed the possibility of establishing safe zones in Syria. President Trump emphasized the commitment to strengthening the security and economic partnership with Jordan and praised Jordan's role as a model of tolerance and moderation in the region. They also discussed the King returning to Washington for an official visit in the future.